Your 3NT call would not have been my choice.  Too many negatives: not a
legitmate heart stopper or decent diamond holding.  I wouldn't have bid 2D
or 2C either as both these bids send the wrong message.  Assuming you were
playing 2/1 gf (you didn't say), my call would have been a forcing 1NT and
take it from there.

But your having bid 3NT, I believe your partner's 4NT can only be described
as pusillanamous.  I would have called 6S or 6NT.  He has 18 hcp with a good
6 card suit.  He has 3 aces, which beckons a suit contract, and makes it
highly unlikely that the opponents can cash two quick tricks.  I'd just call
6S after your 3NT.

