a) That 3NT bid is horrid.  The 3NT reply to 1-of-a-suit has been
called, with good reason, the most stultifying call in bridge.  It is
for that reason that 3NT, whether natural or conventional, should
conform to very rigid requirements.  It is not a bid to be sought after
just because you are a hand hog.

b) And partner was stultified.  With 18 HCP, a 6-card suit (that has
been &quot;supported&quot; by 3NT), and massive controls.  The only concern about
bidding 6S directly over 3NT is the spade quality.  Surely you and your
5K MP partner have a way to check that.

