I would give you 50% of the blame for not getting to 6S.
Your 3NT bid is out of line.
Why do you make these bids?
You have no heart stopper.
You really don't want to play 3NT without exploring other contracts.
I would bid 2C where 7/13 of my hcp. But even after a 2D response your
side would probably get 6S with little effort.

As for you partner, I would find his 4NT bid on the conservative side.
He would have made the same bid with one less spade and one more
heart. Also, he doesn't need for you to have a maximum to make 6S. For
example,
S Qx   H Kxxx   D xxx   D AKxx. Since his spade intermediates are so
good and he has six of them, I would at least bid 5S as an
invitational bid but I would probably just say to hell with it and bid
6S.

In short,  your partner should probably bid more than 4NT. But if he
were playing with one of his peers who would normally not bid 3NT they
would get to 6S easily. Your 3NT bid created unnecessary conditions
for partner to make a mistake and he did. But you share the blame for
bidding 3NT.

Eric Leong
