I don't care for this treatment. 3NT is too space consuming and will
often leave opener guessing whether to try play 3NT or 4M or 5m. For
example, had partner held: AQJxx, x, AKxx, xxx he would pass 3NT for a
disastrous result. We could blame that on your offbeat 3NT call but
that is not the root of the problem. Even if you had held a more
normal 3NT bid, opener would have to guess whether you held a half,
single or a double heart stopper opposite his stiff. On a bad day you
would have Kx, Qxx, QJxx, AQxx.

It is better to use 2NT to show a balanced 13-15. When opener has some
shape, he has room to explore for the best game contract below 3NT. It
is also better for slam auctions. Of course this means you can't use
Jacoby, but 1S-P-3C and 1H-P-2S can be used to show the Jacoby hand.

